sentences: Tim Eyermann (1947-May 1, 2007) was a saxophonist, known for his work with The Airmen of Note and as a recording musician.
In 1974, he formed a band called the East Coast Offering.
In 1999 Tim released his most recent album Karla's Fire.
He died on May 1, 2007, due to complications in surgery, pneumonia spread throughout his body while trying to remove a malignant cancer in his lung.
He started his musical career at the age of six by taking up piano lessons for two years, he hated them.
He was so inspired, he picked up the alto saxophone and within two years many people say that he was playing professionally.
After graduating from Duquesne University, Eyermann spent six years in the United States Air Force, playing with the NORAD Band and eventually the U.S. Air Force's  Airmen of Note.
Tim used Summit Records for many years.
Around 2000–2002 Eyermann moved to Miami, Florida.
